---
import DocsLayout from "../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { compilerVersion, languageLabel, vscodeExtensionMarketplaceUrl } from "../config/version";
import { sitePath } from "../lib/playground/links";

const frontmatter = {
  title: "Tooling",
  description: "DCL compiler, language server, VS Code extension, playground, and MCP server tooling.",
};
---

<DocsLayout frontmatter={frontmatter}>
  <h1>DCL Tooling</h1>
  <p>
    DCL tooling is local-first and compiler-backed. The same Go compiler powers
    command-line validation, the language server, the VS Code extension, the
    browser playground, and the MCP server for AI clients.
  </p>
  <p>
    Current language: <strong>{languageLabel}</strong>. Compiler:
    <code>dcl {compilerVersion}</code>.
  </p>

  <h2>Command-Line Tools</h2>
  <table class="reference-table">
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Binary</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>dcl</code></td><td>Compiler CLI for version, validation, and IR output.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>dcl-lsp</code></td><td>Language server for editor diagnostics, navigation, symbols, and references.</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>dcl-mcp</code></td><td>Local stdio MCP server for AI clients such as Claude Desktop, Claude Code, VS Code MCP clients, and other MCP-compatible tools.</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>MCP Server</h2>
  <p>
    <code>dcl-mcp</code> exposes read-only compiler-backed tools for validating
    DCL workspaces, explaining diagnostics, generating IR, and summarizing the
    semantic model. It does not require hosting, authentication, HTTP transport,
    or cloud services.
  </p>
  <p>
    Setup instructions, client configuration examples, troubleshooting, and the
    MCP roadmap are maintained in the repository documentation.
  </p>
  <div class="actions">
    <a class="button primary" href="https://github.com/russelleast/Capability-Language/blob/main/docs/mcp.md">MCP setup guide</a>
    <a class="button secondary" href="https://github.com/russelleast/Capability-Language/blob/main/docs/mcp-roadmap.md">MCP roadmap</a>
  </div>

  <h2>VS Code Extension</h2>
  <p>
    The VS Code extension bundles the compiler and language server for supported
    platforms. It provides syntax highlighting, compile commands, diagnostics,
    semantic navigation, and architecture graph views.
  </p>
  <div class="actions">
    <a class="button primary" href={vscodeExtensionMarketplaceUrl}>Install from Marketplace</a>
  </div>

  <h2>Playground</h2>
  <p>
    The browser playground is the fastest way to try DCL examples, inspect
    compiler diagnostics, and view the semantic model without installing local
    tools.
  </p>
  <div class="actions">
    <a class="button secondary" href={sitePath("/playground/")}>Open Playground</a>
  </div>
</DocsLayout>
